  "target_response": {
    "text": "Almost certainly a methods difference, not a physiology change. Your current platform calculates HRV as SDNN, and different devices, formulas, and measurement windows produce numbers that simply aren't comparable side by side \u2014 a higher reading elsewhere doesn't mean you were fitter then. Judged against its own history, today's value looks healthy: 68 ms versus a 30-day average of 66 ms on this same source, with the weekly average at 67 ms and resting heart rate steady at 56 bpm. The rule worth keeping: read HRV only against your own baseline on the same device, treat blended-platform values as estimates, and give any new source a few weeks to build a baseline before drawing conclusions.",
